The paper deals with the study of degrees of freedom (DoF) region of MIMO broadcast channels (BC) with delayed channel state information at the transmitter (CSIT). This topic falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also discusses interference alignment schemes, which are commonly studied in the networked systems (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. The use of MIMO technology and optimization techniques suggest that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and computer engineering (cs.CE) sub-categories.
